(system_prompt='\nYou are an expert insurance education quiz designer specializing in LOMA certification exams.\n\nYou will receive 1 category group(s), each with its own text chunks.\nCreate exactly 1 multiple-choice question per category group вҖ” 1 question(s) total.\n\nDIFFICULTY DISTRIBUTION:\n   - Beginner: exactly 1 question(s)\n\nв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\nQUESTION TYPE & DIFFICULTY CLASSIFICATION\nв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n\nThere are 4 question types. Each maps to a difficulty level as described below.\nUse these definitions to select BOTH the question_type AND difficulty for each question.\n\nв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nTYPE 1 вҖ” Definition / Concept                    вҶ’ BEGINNER\nв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nPurpose:\n  Directly test knowledge of specific terms, their meanings,\n  and fundamental principles or characteristics.\n\nCharacteristics:\n  вҖў Require recalling definitions, rules, or attributes of a concept.\n  вҖў Typical stems: "What is X?", "Which best defines Y?",\n    "Which statement accurately describes Z?"\n  вҖў Focus on factual understanding, NOT application in a complex context.\n\nExample question:\n  Risk is the possibility of an unexpected result. Risks can be speculative\n  risks or pure risks. (Speculative / Pure) risk is an insurable risk because\n  there is (a / no) possibility of gain.\n    A: Speculative / a\n    B: Speculative / no\n    C: Pure / a\n    D: Pure / no  вҶҗ correct\n\nв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nTYPE 2 вҖ” Application of Definitions              вҶ’ INTERMEDIATE\nв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nPurpose:\n  Take a known definition and use its criteria to accurately\n  analyze, classify, or explain a specific scenario or example.\n\nCharacteristics:\n  вҖў The candidate must know the definition AND apply it correctly.\n  вҖў Typically presents statements and asks which is correct/incorrect.\n  вҖў Context is familiar and single-layered.\n\nExample question:\n  The following statements are about contractual capacity in the formation\n  of insurance contracts. Select the answer choice containing the correct statement.\n    A: An insurer acquires its legal capacity to issue an insurance contract\n       by being licensed or authorized to do business by the proper regulatory authority. вҶҗ correct\n    B: If an insurer issues a policy to a person who is younger than the permissible\n       age to purchase insurance, the insurer can avoid the policy.\n    C: An insurance contract entered into by a person when the person\'s mental\n       competence is impaired, but who has not been declared insane or mentally\n       incompetent by a court, is a valid contract.\n    D: An insurance contract entered into by a person after a court has declared\n       the person to be insane or mentally incompetent is a voidable contract.\n\nв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nTYPE 3 вҖ” Discriminating Between Complex Concepts вҶ’ INTERMEDIATE\nв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nPurpose:\n  Test the ability to identify subtle yet crucial distinctions between\n  two or more closely related or potentially overlapping concepts.\n\nCharacteristics:\n  вҖў Presents two or more items (contracts, terms, situations) side by side.\n  вҖў Candidate must correctly label or classify EACH one.\n  вҖў Concepts are closely related and easily confused.\n\nExample question:\n  The following information describes two contracts:\n    Contract A вҖ” one of the parties has the legal right to reject her obligations\n                 under the contract without incurring legal liability.\n    Contract B вҖ” does not meet one of the legal requirements to create a legally\n                 enforceable contract.\n  Select the response that correctly indicates whether these contracts are void or voidable:\n    A: void / void\n    B: void / voidable\n    C: voidable / voidable\n    D: voidable / void  вҶҗ correct\n\nв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nTYPE 4 вҖ” Scenario-based / Situational            вҶ’ INTERMEDIATE or ADVANCED\nв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nPurpose:\n  Present a hypothetical situation or story and require applying knowledge\n  of terms, principles, or rules to that specific context.\n\nCharacteristics:\n  вҖў Asks the candidate to: identify the correct term describing a situation,\n    choose the correct decision/action/legal outcome, differentiate similar\n    concepts by seeing which fits the scenario, or analyze implications\n    using specific terminology.\n\nDifficulty rules:\n  вҖў INTERMEDIATE вҖ” single scenario, one concept to identify or apply,\n    straightforward mapping from fact to term.\n  вҖў ADVANCED вҖ” multi-fact scenario requiring classification of EACH fact\n    independently, OR multi-step reasoning, OR precise discrimination\n    among very similar options.\n\nExample (ADVANCED):\n  Carly Pavin, an underwriter for Keen Insurance Company, has gathered the\n  following information about Van Gregg, a proposed insured:\n    Fact A: Mr. Gregg is overweight and has high blood pressure.\n    Fact B: Mr. Gregg was convicted of tax evasion five years ago.\n  Select the response that correctly classifies Facts A and B as moral hazards\n  or medical risk factors:\n    A: Factor A: moral hazard.        Factor B: medical risk factor\n    B: Factor A: moral hazard.        Factor B: moral hazard\n    C: Factor A: medical risk factor. Factor B: medical risk factor\n    D: Factor A: medical risk factor. Factor B: moral hazard  вҶҗ correct\n\nExample (ADVANCED вҖ” multi-statement):\n  Lila Tabak is the policyowner-insured of a life insurance contract with\n  Elm Insurance Company. Which of the following statement(s) can correctly\n  be made about this contract?\n    Statement A: Ms. Tabak\'s contract with Elm is an example of a formal,\n                 rather than an informal, contract.\n    Statement B: If any provision in this contract is ambiguous, the courts\n                 most likely will interpret that provision against Elm.\n    A: Both A and B\n    B: A only\n    C: B only  вҶҗ correct\n    D: Neither A nor B\n\nв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\nDIFFICULTY SUMMARY\nв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n\n  Beginner     вҶ’ Type 1 (Definition / Concept) only\n  Intermediate вҶ’ Type 2 (Application of Definitions)\n                 Type 3 (Discriminating Between Complex Concepts)\n                 Type 4 (Scenario-based, single-layer)\n  Advanced     вҶ’ Type 4 (Scenario-based, multi-fact / multi-step / multi-statement)\n\nв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\nRULES\nв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n\n1. Base all questions STRICTLY on the provided chunks вҖ” no outside knowledge.\n2. Each question must have exactly 4 options (index 0вҖ“3) with ONE correct answer.\n3. Assign question_type and difficulty strictly per the classification above,\n   AND respect any DIFFICULTY DISTRIBUTION constraints in DIFFICULTY DISTRIBUTION:\n   - Beginner: exactly 1 question(s).\n4. Wrong options must be plausible, clearly distinct, and represent realistic mistakes.\n5. For "sources", copy file_name exactly as it appears in chunk metadata; set "url" to "".\n6. Return ONLY valid JSON вҖ” no markdown fences, no commentary before or after.\n\nв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\nOUTPUT FORMAT\nв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n\n{\n  "questions": [\n    {\n      "category": "<category>",\n      "node_name": "<node_name from chunks>",\n      "question_type": "<Definition / Concept | Application of Definitions | Discriminating Between Complex Concepts | Scenario-based / Situational>",\n      "difficulty": "<Beginner | Intermediate | Advanced>",\n      "question": "<question text>",\n      "options": [\n        {"index": 0, "text": "<option text>"},\n        {"index": 1, "text": "<option text>"},\n        {"index": 2, "text": "<option text>"},\n        {"index": 3, "text": "<option text>"}\n      ],\n      "correct_answer": <0|1|2|3>,\n      "explanation": "<why the correct answer is right>",\n      "hint": "<short hint without revealing the answer>",\n      "traps": {\n        "description": "<common mistakes learners make on this question>",\n        "wrong_reasons": [\n          {"index": <int>, "reason": "<why this option is wrong>"}\n        ]\n      },\n      "correct_reason": "<detailed step-by-step reasoning for the correct answer>",\n      "sources": [\n        {\n          "name": "<file_name>",\n          "url": "",\n          "page": <int>,\n          "total_pages": <int>,\n          "module": "<str>",\n          "lesson": "<str>"\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n', messages=[{'role': 'user', 'content': "в•җв•җв•җ Node: Term Life Insurance | Category: Product Type в•җв•җв•җ\nDefinition  : Life insurance that provides a death benefit only if the insured dies during the period specified in the policy. It offers temporary financial protection for a set term.\nRelated Nodes: KN-002, KN-003, KN-004, KN-008, KN-009, KN-010\n\nв”Җв”Җ Chunks в”Җв”Җ\n--- Chunk 1 ---\nfile_name   : LOMA281_M2L1_Knowledge File_Term Life Insurance\npage_number : 19\ntotal_pages : 23\nmodule      : 2\nlesson      : 1\ncourse      : LOMA281\ntext:\nExplanation: Renewal coverage can be for the same face amount as the\noriginal policy or smaller, but not for a larger face amount.\n2. When a term life insurance policy is RENEWED, the coverage period\ncan ...\n\uf071\nincrease\n\uf071\ndecrease\n\uf071\nremain the same\nAnswer: decrease, remain the same\nExplanation: Renewal coverage term can be same length as the original\npolicy or shorter, but not longer.\n3. When a term life insurance policy is RENEWED, the premium rate (for\nthe same amount of coverage) can ...\n\uf071\nincrease\n\uf071\n--- Chunk 2 ---\nfile_name   : LOMA281_M2L1_Knowledge File_Term Life Insurance\npage_number : 20\ntotal_pages : 23\nmodule      : 2\nlesson      : 1\ncourse      : LOMA281\ntext:\nExplanation: The type of coverage before and after renewal remains the\nsame.\n5. When a term life insurance policy is CONVERTED, the amount of\ncoverage can ...\n\uf071\nincrease\n\uf071\ndecrease\n\uf071\nremain the same\nAnswer: decrease, remains the same\nExplanation: The insurer may allow conversion for the full amount of, or a\npercentage of, the original policy.\n6. When a term life insurance policy is CONVERTED,the coverage period\ncan ...\n\uf071\nincrease\n\uf071\ndecrease\n\uf071\nremain the same\nAnswer: increase\n--- Chunk 3 ---\nfile_name   : LOMA281_M2L1_Knowledge File_Term Life Insurance\npage_number : 22\ntotal_pages : 23\nmodule      : 2\nlesson      : 1\ncourse      : LOMA281\ntext:\n_Trang nГ y khГҙng cГі nб»ҷi dung vДғn bбәЈn hay бәЈnh dб»Ҝ liб»Үu._\n--- Chunk 4 ---\nfile_name   : LOMA281_M2L1_Knowledge File_Term Life Insurance\npage_number : 2\ntotal_pages : 23\nmodule      : 2\nlesson      : 1\ncourse      : LOMA281\ntext:\nFinally, life insurance proceeds can support the family until Bridget can find\nnew sources of income or can adjust to a lower income.\nWhat is Term Life?\nCarter needs financial protection for his wife and children in case he should\ndie unexpectedly. His wife Bridget also needs financial protection for Carter\nand the children.\n--- Chunk 5 ---\nfile_name   : LOMA281_M2L1_Knowledge File_Term Life Insurance\npage_number : 1\ntotal_pages : 23\nmodule      : 2\nlesson      : 1\ncourse      : LOMA281\ntext:\nModule 2: Individual Insurance Products\nLesson 1: Term Life Insurance\nLearning Objectives\nAfter studying this lesson, you will be able to:\n\uf0b7\nDescribe term life insurance (bбәЈo hiб»ғm tб»ӯkб»і) coverage (phбәЎm vi bбәЈo\nhiб»ғm) and distinguish between level term (tб»ӯkб»іcб»‘Д‘б»Ӣnh), decreasing\nterm (tб»ӯkб»іgiбәЈm dбә§n), and increasing term (tб»ӯkб»іtДғng dбә§n) life\ninsurance plans.\n\uf0b7\nDescribe the operation of a return of premium (ROP) term policy\n(cГЎch hoбәЎt Д‘б»ҷng cб»§a bбәЈo hiб»ғm tб»ӯkб»іhoГ n phГӯ)\n\uf0b7\n--- Chunk 6 ---\nfile_name   : LOMA281_M2L1_Knowledge File_Term Life Insurance\npage_number : 23\ntotal_pages : 23\nmodule      : 2\nlesson      : 1\ncourse      : LOMA281\ntext:\n_Trang nГ y khГҙng cГі nб»ҷi dung vДғn bбәЈn hay бәЈnh dб»Ҝ liб»Үu._\n--- Chunk 7 ---\nfile_name   : LOMA281_M2L1_Knowledge File_Term Life Insurance\npage_number : 2\ntotal_pages : 23\nmodule      : 2\nlesson      : 1\ncourse      : LOMA281\ntext:\n\uf071Providing financial support for the family\n\uf071Funding a childвҖҷs education\nAnswer: All is correct\nExplanation: Proceeds can help cover household expenses and expenses\nrelated to CarterвҖҷs death that arenвҖҷt covered by other insurance. CarterвҖҷs\nwife Bridget wonвҖҷt have to sell assets from CarterвҖҷs estate to pay off his\ndebts; she can also use the proceeds to pay any private school and/or college.\nFinally, life insurance proceeds can support the family until Bridget can find\n--- Chunk 8 ---\nfile_name   : LOMA281_M2L1_Knowledge File_Term Life Insurance\npage_number : 19\ntotal_pages : 23\nmodule      : 2\nlesson      : 1\ncourse      : LOMA281\ntext:\nthe same amount of coverage) can ...\n\uf071\nincrease\n\uf071\ndecrease\n\uf071\nremain the same\nAnswer: increase\nExplanation: Renewal premium rate is based on the insured's attained age\nat renewal and so is higher than original premium rate.\n4. When a term life insurance policy is RENEWED, the type of coverage ...\n\uf071\nchanges\n\uf071\nremains the same\nAnswer: remains the same\n--- Chunk 9 ---\nfile_name   : LOMA281_M2L1_Knowledge File_Term Life Insurance\npage_number : 3\ntotal_pages : 23\nmodule      : 2\nlesson      : 1\ncourse      : LOMA281\ntext:\nTerm life insurance (Life insurance that provides a death benefit only if the\ninsured dies during the period specified in the policy.), which provides\ncoverage for a specified period of time, is one product that could help meet\nCarterвҖҷs needs.\nNo. For starters, the policy term varies from policy to policy. Three\nexamples:\n\uf0b7\nFlight insurance that insures a passenger's life during one airplane trip\n\uf0b7\nA life insurance policy that insures a person for 20 years\n\uf0b7\n--- Chunk 10 ---\nfile_name   : LOMA281_M2L1_Knowledge File_Term Life Insurance\npage_number : 1\ntotal_pages : 23\nmodule      : 2\nlesson      : 1\ncourse      : LOMA281\ntext:\n(cГЎch hoбәЎt Д‘б»ҷng cб»§a bбәЈo hiб»ғm tб»ӯkб»іhoГ n phГӯ)\n\uf0b7\nExplain how the renewal (gia hбәЎn) and conversion (chuyб»ғn Д‘б»•i)\nfeatures included in some term life policies increase their value to\ncustomers.\nTerm Life Insurance\nLearning Objective\nDescribe term life insurance coverage and distinguish between level term,\ndecreasing term, and increasing term life insurance plans.\n--- Chunk 11 ---\nfile_name   : LOMA281_M2L1_Knowledge File_Term Life Insurance\npage_number : 2\ntotal_pages : 23\nmodule      : 2\nlesson      : 1\ncourse      : LOMA281\ntext:\nFinancial Needs Met by Life Insurance\n(Nhu cбә§u tГ i chГӯnh Д‘ГЎp б»©ng bб»ҹi cГҙng ty bбәЈo hiб»ғm)\nWhat do you think\nAssume that Carter has life insurance on his own life. Select the box beside\neach financial need that you think life insurance can meet.\n\uf071Paying household expenses (utility bills, food, clothing, etc.)\n\uf071Covering outstanding debts (mortgage and car loans, etc.)\n\uf071Paying future outstanding medical, hospital, and funeral expenses\n\uf071Providing financial support for the family\n\uf071Funding a childвҖҷs education\n--- Chunk 12 ---\nfile_name   : LOMA281_M2L1_Knowledge File_Term Life Insurance\npage_number : 12\ntotal_pages : 23\nmodule  